### Technologies Used

- **Language**: Rust
- **Blockchain**: Base (Ethereum L2)
- **DEX**: Uniswap V3, Aerodrome
- **RPC**: Web3 Providers
- **Monitored Tokens**: USDC, WETH, DAI, USDbC, cbBTC, AERO, wstETH, USDT, cbETH, BRETT, DEGEN, TOSHI


## ğŸ“Š Experimental Results

After several weeks of testing:
- **Opportunities detected**: ~5-10 per day
- **Profitable opportunities**: 0
- **Profit made**: $0

## ğŸš€ Installation 

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/base-arbitrage-bot.git
cd base-arbitrage-bot

# Install Rust
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh

# Configure environment variables
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your RPC_URL and PRIVATE_KEY

# Build the project
cargo build --release

# Run the bot (dry-run mode recommended)
cargo run --release
```

## âš™ï¸ Configuration

The `config.json` file contains:
- List of monitored tokens with their priorities
- Pool parameters (Uniswap fees, minimum liquidity)
- Filters (minimum liquidity, maximum price impact)

